{"schema_version":"1.7.3","id":"OESA-2024-1502","published":"2024-04-26T11:07:50Z","modified":"2025-09-03T06:20:15.850234Z","upstream":["CVE-2024-32487"],"summary":"less security update","details":"Less is a pager. A pager is a program that displays text files. Other pagers commonly in use are more and pg. Pagers are often used in command-line environments like the Unix shell and the MS-DOS command prompt to display files.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\r\n\r\nless through 653 allows OS command execution via a newline character in the name of a file, because quoting is mishandled in filename.c. Exploitation typically requires use with attacker-controlled file names, such as the files extracted from an untrusted archive. Exploitation also requires the LESSOPEN environment variable, but this is set by default in many common cases.(CVE-2024-32487)","affected":[{"package":{"name":"less","ecosystem":"openEuler:20.03-LTS-SP1","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/less&distro=openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP1"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"590-4.oe1"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["less-debuginfo-590-4.oe1.aarch64.rpm","less-590-4.oe1.aarch64.rpm","less-debugsource-590-4.oe1.aarch64.rpm"],"noarch":["less-help-590-4.oe1.noarch.rpm"],"src":["less-590-4.oe1.src.rpm"],"x86_64":["less-debugsource-590-4.oe1.x86_64.rpm","less-590-4.oe1.x86_64.rpm","less-debuginfo-590-4.oe1.x86_64.rpm"]},"database_specific":{"source":"https://repo.openeuler.org/security/data/osv/OESA-2024-1502.json"}},{"package":{"name":"less","ecosystem":"openEuler:22.03-LTS","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/less&distro=openEuler-22.03-LTS"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"590-6.oe2203sp3"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["less-590-6.oe2203.aarch64.rpm","less-debuginfo-590-6.oe2203.aarch64.rpm","less-debugsource-590-6.oe2203.aarch64.rpm","less-590-6.oe2203sp2.aarch64.rpm","less-debugsource-590-6.oe2203sp2.aarch64.rpm","less-debuginfo-590-6.oe2203sp2.aarch64.rpm"